race.comment: A plain maiden to kick things off. PAZYRYK (8) has not raced since being well in commission on debut at Canterbury last February but failing to figure. Now in the Michael Freedman yard and her two trials since coming across have been encouraging. Suspect she has the talent to stretch this field. AT HER MERCY (5) raced on the speed then found plenty when asked but found one better when resuming over this distance in a $50k maiden at Wagga last start. Won't find this any harder so she comes right into calculations. MAJESTIC LEGEND (12) has been freshened up since failing over 1100m at Gosford seven weeks ago. Ran a couple of nice races over today's journey prior to that. Should play a major role. ANDHE'S BRAVE (10) strips fitter after a couple of modest efforts so far this prep. Exotics only. VINGT NEUF NOIR (14) will find this easier than recent assignments. Capable of a spike in form.
